Review taken during phase 1 of Covid, so take with a grain of salt if you are reading this once life is normal. Unfortunately, a pretty unimpressive first experience.  Ordered take out during phase 1 of Covid. The woman  who took the order over the phone was kind and patient. Upon arriving, a party of 8 was seated right at the entrance of the building and quite impossible to maintain 6 feet of distances upon entry. Strike 1. Moving forward, got the food and headed home. Upon getting home, received a phone call that they had forgotten our $14 appetizer. Strike 2. Was told we can go back to grab it, but after already having to get way to close to the party of 8, we asked for a refund. Was told that they struggle with refunds, and if they could, it could take 2 weeks. Strike 3. Food was unremarkable and the experience very unsatisfactory. The only thing preventing this from being a 1 star review is due to a lot of these issues being due to covid and being a takeout order. Regardless, I don't see this being better than a 3 star restaurant, and overpriced for the quality.
